Background on West Nile virus in Mexico
---------------------------------------
[The following information on West Nile virus in Mexico has been extracted
from the GIDEON database for ProMED-mail by M Berger. - Mod.CP]
A case of West Nile fever (fatal, imported from Texas) was reported in
Coahuila in 2002.
Infected birds were identified in Nuevo Laredo, San Pedro, Pesqueria, Los
Aldamas, and Marin early in 2003 -- the first reports in the Americas for 2003.
Serological evidence of West Nile virus infection was reported in 62.5 per
cent of horses in Coahuila and 1.2 per cent of horses in Yucatan States in
2002. In 2003, equine infection was reported in Chihuahua, Tamaulipas,
Coahuila, Veracruz, Tabasco, Quintana Roo, and Yucatan.
--
M Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
